

---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="alchemy"
  description="alchemy index / nigredo, albedo, rubedo, transformation, philosopher's stone"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-kicker">alchemy / archive wing / index</div>
    <h1>alchemy</h1>
    <p>
      blackening, whitening, reddening, dissolution, refinement, and the slow work
      of inner transformation. alchemy speaks in metals, fire, vessels, ash, gold,
      and impossible substances because ordinary language is often too thin.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      this wing treats alchemy as both symbolic psychology and sacred process:
      decomposition, clarification, recombination, and the making of something
      more whole.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">entry sequence</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <div class="grid-links">
        <a href="/alchemy/nigredo">
          <span class="link-title">nigredo</span>
          <span class="link-desc">blackening, breakdown, descent, confusion, and necessary ruin.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/alchemy/albedo">
          <span class="link-title">albedo</span>
          <span class="link-desc">whitening, purification, reflection, and emerging clarity.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/alchemy/rubedo">
          <span class="link-title">rubedo</span>
          <span class="link-desc">reddening, embodiment, completion, and living integration.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/alchemy/transformation">
          <span class="link-title">transformation</span>
          <span class="link-desc">change of form, process, trial, and inner reconfiguration.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/alchemy/philosophers-stone">
          <span class="link-title">philosopher's stone</span>
          <span class="link-desc">the hidden goal, impossible substance, and image of totality.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">how to read</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p>
        do not read alchemy as if it were only primitive chemistry or only metaphor.
        it works through overlap. matter, psyche, suffering, spirit, and transformation
        are mirrored through one another.
      </p>
      <p>
        the best way to move through this section is in sequence. each stage changes
        the meaning of the next.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">alchemy map</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p><a href="/alchemy/nigredo" class="link-blue">nigredo</a> — darkness, breakdown, putrefaction</p>
      <p><a href="/alchemy/albedo" class="link-red">albedo</a> — purification, washing, clearing</p>
      <p><a href="/alchemy/rubedo" class="link-green">rubedo</a> — embodiment, completion, living fire</p>
      <p><a href="/alchemy/transformation">transformation</a> — process, death and rebirth, re-forming</p>
      <p><a href="/alchemy/philosophers-stone">philosopher's stone</a> — totality, incorruptible center, final symbol</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">note</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p class="muted">
        this wing is arranged as a circular path: nigredo → albedo → rubedo →
        transformation → philosopher's stone → back to nigredo.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>